::USGOV-U01-L02-Q01::Which reason best explains why governments form? {
~To increase confusion and disorder#Incorrect. Governments form to reduce disorder, not increase it.
~To eliminate all cooperation among people#Incorrect. Governments help people cooperate and work together.
~To prevent communities from having rules#Incorrect. Governments create rules to organize society.
=To maintain order and support society#Correct. Maintaining order is one of the main reasons governments form.
}

::USGOV-U01-L02-Q02::What does it mean when government promotes the common good? {
=It makes choices that benefit society as a whole#Correct. The common good refers to benefits for the broader community.
~It only helps one individual at a time#Incorrect. The common good focuses on society as a whole, not one person only.
~It removes all laws from society#Incorrect. Removing all laws would not support the common good.
~It avoids making public decisions#Incorrect. Governments promote the common good by making decisions for society.
}

::USGOV-U01-L02-Q03::Why is protection one reason governments form? {
=Because governments help protect citizens from harm#Correct. Protection and safety are core functions of government.
~Because people do not need safety without government#Incorrect. Safety and protection are key reasons government exists.
~Because protection removes the need for cooperation#Incorrect. Protection and cooperation can both be reasons governments form.
~Because only private groups can protect communities#Incorrect. Governments also play a major protective role.
}

::USGOV-U01-L02-Q04::How do governments support cooperation? {
~By encouraging people to work against each other#Incorrect. Governments help organize people to work together.
=By creating shared systems and rules#Correct. Shared systems and rules help cooperation happen.
~By preventing communities from organizing services#Incorrect. Governments often help organize public services.
~By removing all expectations for public behavior#Incorrect. Expectations and rules support cooperation.
}

::USGOV-U01-L02-Q05::Which statement best reflects the full lesson idea? {
~Governments form only to punish wrongdoing#Incorrect. The lesson includes order, protection, cooperation, and the common good.
~Governments form mainly to avoid responsibility#Incorrect. Governments are formed to organize and support society.
=Governments form to maintain order, provide protection, support cooperation, and promote the common good#Correct. This is the complete summary of the lesson.
~Governments form so people never need to work together#Incorrect. Governments support cooperation, not separation.
}
